  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Water Interventions for Somali Refugees in Dolo Ado Woreda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project entails water trucking operations for approximately a four-month period to supply water to residents in Kobe Camp while a permanent system is being established. In parallel with the water trucking activity, the project includes improvements to and further development of the Kobe Camp permanent water supply system, specifically the construction of the water intake structure, pump station, and water treatment plant, as well as the installation of a distribution system and tap stands within the camp.</narrative>
  </description>
